11. A play of Plautus bears a rather greater likeness to an opera of the early schools than to a drama of to-day. There are spoken parts (Diverbium) and sung parts (Canticum), the latter being divided into Recitative and Sonq proper. An actor might gesticulate a song-part which a singer behind the soenes would render.
